we heritage.This sophisticated analysis is of use to students and readers at all levels of engagement with Erdrich’s writing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Women Authors.2bisacsh  aLouise Erdrich.  aNative American literature.  aNative American writers.  aOjibwe.  aaesthetics.  achildren's writing.  aethics.  amemoir.  apoetry.  atextual complexities.1 aStirrup, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779348540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847793485423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847793485/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles